how do you scrunch your hair should you have a middle part or a side part you can scrunch your hair three ways you can use sprunch spray hair spray or egg whites when you use sprunch spray you apply it to wet damp hair and scrunch it while you are blow drying it scrunch it before during and after you blow dry your hair when you use hair spray you pretty much do the same thing but you have to use a whole lot more spray when you use egg whites you take and crack eggs so they have a small hole and let the whites drain into a bowl you will need several eggs while your hair is damp scrunch your hair while apply the egg whites to it put them all over in your hair and make sure you don't get it on your forehead once you feel you have enough all through your hair start to blow dry it don't brush your hair after or during this or else it will be a complete mess your hair should be scrunched and kinda hard this will wash out by just taking a shower like you normally would if you need anymore help contact me xoxo ella hope i helped ps do a side part Kodocha Brush Aerial (dance move) Textile manufacturing Casting Pottery Thermal power station Japanese toilet Fire fighting Tempera Social rule Motorcycle Instant coffee Air conditioning Car washing techniques Upholstery Customs and etiquette of Japan Diseases of the honeybee Cruising (maritime) Toilet humour Haircut Sushi 2003 United States Grand Prix Seismic retrofit Laws of cricket Fire extinguisher Pepper spray The Amber Spyglass Sento Treehouse of Horror IX Car handling The Ashlee Simpson Show Toilet paper The Grim Adventures of Billy and Mandy Drawing Sauna Hair Great Teacher Onizuka Concrete Happy Tree Friends Urinary incontinence K' Poker jargon Bulk vending Pysanka Champagne (beverage) Haloalkane Shampoo Glass Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Dundas Square Mohawk hairstyle Printed circuit board Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Towel Bedbug Gas metal arc welding Friction 2000 Australian Grand Prix Knife Linen Tarantula T